news.title: Maharashtra: Police to get powers to crack down on illegal sand mining
news.para: Bawankule said the policy would be released within a week while responding to supplementary questions on unauthorised river sand mining in the Godavari river in Sambhajinagar during the question hour.

news.title: JK Lakshmi Cement gets Rs 45.6 crore demand from income tax authority
news.para: Based on preliminary assessment of the issues involved, JK Lakshmi Cement said it is of "the view that the demand is fallacious, legally untenable and would be set aside in the course of proceedings".

news.title: Telangana high court orders status quo on land acquisition for industrial park
news.para: The state and its revenue authorities filed two appeals against the stay order and urged the court to allow them to acquire land for the project.

news.title: US single-family homebuilding surge 11.4% in February
news.para: President Donald Trump this month imposed and later suspended a 25% tariff on most goods from Canada and Mexico, which would have pushed up U.S. duties on Canadian lumber to nearly 40%.

news.title: Smartworks rents 2.2 lakh sq ft office space at DLF Cyber City in Hyderabad
news.para: The new space addition brings the company's total footprint in Hyderabad, Telangana, to over one million (10 lakh) square feet.

news.title: Prayagraj development body cracks down on unauthorised construction
news.para: To get the map approved, the entire PDA team interacts with aspirants to solve their problems and grievances. If any kind of building construction work is done by the building owner without getting the map approved, then buildings can be sealed.

news.title: Haryana CM announces affordable rental housing for migrants
news.para: The aim of this initiative is to provide financial stability, social security, and improved working conditions for gig workers, enabling them to become more self-reliant and active contributors to Haryana's economic development.

news.title: UN urges rapid cuts in building sector emissions to meet climate goals
news.para: Carbon dioxide emissions from the building sector rose around 5 per cent in the last decade when they should have fallen 28 per cent, according to a new report by the United Nations Environment Programme (UNEP).

news.title: Japan's land prices surge 2.7% in January 2024
news.para: Average nationwide land prices, across residential and commercial, grew 2.7% as of January 1, the fourth straight year of gains, the land ministry survey showed.

news.title: About 34 entities settle Shalimar Paints takeover norms violation case with Sebi
news.para: While examining Draft Letter of Offer filed for the acquisition of equity shares of Shalimar Paints by Hella Infra Market Private Limited, Sebi had observed that 1,65,545 equity shares of Shalimar Paints, were acquired by Urvi Jindal.

news.title: CCI approves Ambuja Cements' acquisition of Orient Cement
news.para: Ambuja Cements, India's second-largest cement maker, in October revealed plans to buy stake worth $451 million in Orient Cement, intensifying competition with industry leader UltraTech Cement.

news.title: Cement sales likely to grow by 8% in FY25: JK Lakshmi Cement
news.para: As the market consolidates, Arun Shukla, president and director of JK Lakshmi Cement, sees a bright future with higher profitability.

news.title: IWG posts revenue of $4.2 billion in 2024
news.para: Its network grew with 899 new centre signings and 624 openings in 2024. Its net financial debt continued to drop and stood at $712 million in 2024 as against $775 million debt it reported in 2023.

news.title: India remains a high-growth real estate market in Asia Pacific region: Report
news.para: According to the Nasdaq-listed real estate consultancy firm, India saw 88 per cent annual rise in investments at USD 3.0 billion. Office assets continued to draw majority of the investments at 47 per cent share, followed by industrial and logistics at 27 per cent share.

news.title: HC summons Bhopal collector in two cases of contempt over RERA
news.para: Both cases pertain to non-compliance of court directives on execution of RRC issued by Real Estate Regulatory Authority (RERA).

news.title: State government declines formation of metropolitan development body in Kochi
news.para: Replying to a question from TJ Vinod, MLA, LSGD minister MB Rajesh said govt has no plan to form MDA or expand the limit of city corporation.

news.title: Pune civic body launches all-woman team to boost property tax recovery
news.para: On average, PMC collects Rs 2,000 crore as property tax per year. It had set a target of Rs 2,500 crore for the 2024-25 financial year from this levy.

news.title: Housr looks to cross Rs 200 crore revenue in FY26
news.para: Currently operating in five cities, Housr aims to enter Chennai and Mumbai, catering primarily to working professionals.

news.title: Coimbatore to conduct drone-based land survey under DILRMP
news.para: As part of this pilot project, a 10.44 sq. km area will be surveyed using drones, and land records will be updated. Field maps with geo-location points will also be created.

news.title: Ghaziabad: GDA board to take call on developed plots & assimilation of villages
news.para: The meeting, to be chaired by divisional commissioner Hrishikesh Bhaskar Yashod, will take up the proposed assimilation of villages under Hapur Pilakhua and the handover of developed plots to farmers from whom land was acquired for the Madhuban Bapudham housing scheme.
